{{US|reason=harmful}}
This article provides a comparison of core '''mutual funds''' for use in [[Bogleheads investment philosophy|Boglehead-style]] investing. While the choices for [[mutual fund|mutual funds]] depend on the brokerage you use, most modern brokerages offer access to low-cost [[index fund|index mutual funds]], and commission-free access to all [[ETFs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/10/13/battle-for-client-assets-heats-up-as-brokers-cut-fees-to-zero.html|title=Battle for client assets heats up as brokers cut fees to zero|publisher=CNBC|date=October 13, 2019}}</ref> When choosing between [[mutual fund|mutual funds]], the [[expense ratio]] (ER) is an important consideration. This page offers a condensed menu of low-expense-ratio funds that are commonly used as core holdings in the construction of [[lazy portfolios|passive — or "lazy" — portfolios]]. Funds available at each brokerage are compared below.
