==Mutual funds at Charles Schwab==
{{main|Charles Schwab}} 
Charles Schwab manages its own index mutual funds. As a broker, Schwab also provides access to other firm's mutual funds, but they are usually subject to transaction fees (unless the fund is a part of the no-transaction-fee network). {{trim|{{Schwab mutual funds}}}}
All ETFs are commission-free at Schwab, enabling use of low-cost index ETFs. See the [[ETFs for Bogleheads]] article for a comparison of core ETFs.

